---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="Ascend Framework" description="Zeitgeist Ascend: a 5-stage framework for practical AI transformation">
  <section class="pt-20 pb-12">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 max-w-4xl">
      <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold mb-4">Zeitgeist Ascend: A Practical Path to AI Transformation</h1>
      <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-6">A simple, business-first approach to using AI to improve customer experience, product development, and how people work — designed for small and mid-size businesses without large engineering teams.</p>

      <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-lg shadow-sm mb-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-3">Why Ascend?</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700">Many AI projects fail because they start with technology. Ascend starts with value: specific business outcomes you can measure. Then we pick the tools, design the workflows, and make change stick.</p>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">The Five Stages of Ascend</h2>

      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div class="p-4 bg-gray-50 rounded">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold">1. Base Camp — Survey the Summit</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">Define a clear business outcome (your summit) and gather baseline metrics. Focus on one high-impact area — customer experience, product insight, or workforce optimization.</p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-600 mt-2">
            <li>Define 30/60/90 day targets</li>
            <li>Map current performance baselines</li>
            <li>Identify one bottleneck to solve first</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="p-4 bg-gray-50 rounded">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold">2. The Route — Choose Your Gear</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">Pick tools and vendors that match the use case and your team's capacity. Use a simple impact vs effort evaluation so you don't over-buy.</p>
          <p class="text-gray-600 mt-2">Example outputs: chosen tool, integration plan, budget estimate.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="p-4 bg-gray-50 rounded">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold">3. The Climb — Map the Traverse</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">Design the end-to-end workflow that combines AI capabilities with human decisions. Define roles, hand-offs, and quality checks.</p>
          <p class="text-gray-600 mt-2">Example outputs: workflow diagram, roles matrix, training checklist.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="p-4 bg-gray-50 rounded">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold">4. Check Altitude — Track the Ascent</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">Measure progress with a small set of KPIs tied to money, time, or customer experience. Schedule regular reviews and decide when to pivot or scale.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="p-4 bg-gray-50 rounded">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold">5. New Peak — Plant the Flag</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">Standardize the new process, document the lessons, and identify the next high-impact opportunity. Turn pilots into repeatable playbooks.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-4">Ascend Toolkit</h2>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-4">
        <div class="bg-white p-4 rounded shadow-sm">
          <h4 class="font-semibold">Ascent Map</h4>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">One-page planner: peak goal, timeline, selected gear, primary metric.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white p-4 rounded shadow-sm">
          <h4 class="font-semibold">Ascent Log</h4>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Weekly tracker for progress, challenges, and adjustments.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white p-4 rounded shadow-sm">
          <h4 class="font-semibold">Summit Scorecard</h4>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">A compact KPI dashboard template to track efficiency, quality, and business impact.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-8 mb-4">A Practical 30-Day Plan</h2>
      <ol class="list-decimal list-inside text-gray-700">
        <li class="mb-2"><strong>Week 1:</strong> Base Camp — pick the pilot & capture baseline data.</li>
        <li class="mb-2"><strong>Week 2:</strong> The Route — choose a tool, build quick integrations.</li>
        <li class="mb-2"><strong>Week 3:</strong> The Climb — run a short pilot, collect results.</li>
        <li class="mb-2"><strong>Week 4:</strong> Check Altitude — review KPIs, make go/no-go decision.</li>
      </ol>

      <div class="mt-8 text-center">
        <a href="/assessment" class="bg-primary text-white px-6 py-3 rounded-lg mr-3">Take the Free Assessment</a>
        <a href="/webinar" class="border px-6 py-3 rounded-lg">Join the Intro Webinar</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
